<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-25T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-25T04:00:00-05:00" n="528" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d528">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9669: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-25T10:00:00+01:00">August 25, 1937—10
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 25—6:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>386. It is announced today that the first battalion of the 10th
                                Regiment of Savoy Grenadiers left Addis Ababa on August 23 for
                                Massawa, where it will embark for Shanghai to reenforce the San
                                Marco Marine battalion in the defense of Italian interests. It is
                                understood that this battalion is composed of between 600 and 700
                                men, including supply troops.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>